detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: EOSC 314 is a hybrid, asynchronous course for all students. Â All course content is available directly on the course website or through links to outside resources. There is no textbook for this course. All Quizzes and Assignments are open over a set number of days for students to complete when it fits best within their own schedule. These are then submitted online, through the Course Website. There are no lectures to attend or video lectures to follow. The only time students need to attend a session in-person is for the written final exam. The final exam will be written during the UBC exam period, at a time and date arranged by UBC Exam Services. All students will attend the final exam in-person in a UBC classroom.

detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: Educational psychology integrates both the theory of psychology and the practice of education. Â This course will focus on understanding how people learn and grow, while considering items such as motivation, environmental influences and more. As we explore the different ways that people learn we will also consider what it means to learn, how to improve learning (both for ourselves and for others). Â  This course is open to all UBC undergraduate students who are interested in teaching in various contexts and learning about learning.Â
